#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:25
msgid "## `ini_file` module"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:27
msgid ""
"When you want to modify an INI file (section between `[]` then `key=value` "
"pairs), the easiest way is to use the `ini_file` module."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:30
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Note\n"
"    More information can be [found here](https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/collections/community/general/ini_file_module.html).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:32
msgid "The module requires:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:36
msgid "The value of the section"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:36
msgid "The name of the option"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:36
msgid "The new value"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:38
msgid "Example of use:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:47
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```\n"
"- name: change value on inifile\n"
"  community.general.ini_file:\n"
"    dest: /path/to/file.ini\n"
"    section: SECTIONNAME\n"
"    option: OPTIONNAME\n"
"    value: NEWVALUE\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:49
msgid "## `lineinfile` module"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:51
msgid ""
"To ensure that a line is present in a file, or when a single line in a file "
"needs to be added or modified, use the `linefile` module."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:54
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Note\n"
"    More information can be [found here](https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/collections/ansible/builtin/lineinfile_module.html).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:56
msgid ""
"In this case, the line to be modified in a file will be found using a regexp."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:58
msgid ""
"For example, to ensure that the line starting with `SELINUX=` in the `/etc/"
"selinux/config` file contains the value `enforcing`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:65
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```\n"
"- ansible.builtin.lineinfile:\n"
"    path: /etc/selinux/config\n"
"    regexp: '^SELINUX='\n"
"    line: 'SELINUX=enforcing'\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:67
msgid "## `copy` module"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:69
msgid ""
"When a file has to be copied from the Ansible server to one or more hosts, "
"it is better to use the `copy` module."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:72
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Note\n"
"    More information can be [found here](https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/collections/ansible/builtin/copy_module.html).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:74
msgid "Here we are copying `myflile.conf` from one location to another:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:83
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```\n"
"- ansible.builtin.copy:\n"
"    src: /data/ansible/sources/myfile.conf\n"
"    dest: /etc/myfile.conf\n"
"    owner: root\n"
"    group: root\n"
"    mode: 0644\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:85
msgid "## `fetch` module"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:87
msgid ""
"When a file has to be copied from a remote server to the local server, it is "
"best to use the `fetch` module."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:90
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Note\n"
"    More information can be [found here](https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/collections/ansible/builtin/fetch_module.html).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:92
msgid "This module does the opposite of the `copy` module:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:99
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```\n"
"- ansible.builtin.fetch:\n"
"    src: /etc/myfile.conf\n"
"    dest: /data/ansible/backup/myfile-{{ inventory_hostname }}.conf\n"
"    flat: yes\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:101
msgid "## `template` module"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:103
msgid ""
"Ansible and its `template` module use the **Jinja2** template system (http://"
"jinja.pocoo.org/docs/) to generate files on target hosts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:106
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Note\n"
"    More information can be [found here](https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/collections/ansible/builtin/template_module.html).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:117
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```\n"
"- ansible.builtin.template:\n"
"    src: /data/ansible/templates/monfichier.j2\n"
"    dest: /etc/myfile.conf\n"
"    owner: root\n"
"    group: root\n"
"    mode: 0644\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:119
msgid ""
"It is possible to add a validation step if the targeted service allows it "
"(for example apache with the command `apachectl -t`):"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:129
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```\n"
"- template:\n"
"    src: /data/ansible/templates/vhost.j2\n"
"    dest: /etc/httpd/sites-available/vhost.conf\n"
"    owner: root\n"
"    group: root\n"
"    mode: 0644\n"
"    validate: '/usr/sbin/apachectl -t'\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:131
msgid "## `get_url` module"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:133
msgid ""
"To upload files from a web site or ftp to one or more hosts, use the "
"`get_url` module:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:141
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```\n"
"- get_url:\n"
"    url: http://site.com/archive.zip\n"
"    dest: /tmp/archive.zip\n"
"    mode: 0640\n"
"    checksum: sha256:f772bd36185515581aa9a2e4b38fb97940ff28764900ba708e68286121770e9a\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/learning_ansible/03-working-with-files.md:142
msgid ""
"By providing a checksum of the file, the file will not be re-downloaded if "
"it is already present at the destination location and its checksum matches "
"the value provided."
msgstr ""
